INSERT INTO `search_dataset` VALUES (1,'node',' about i need to quickly and effectively document tips and tricks i come across during the countless hours of problem solving some of the information may already exist elsewhere on the web but this site serves as a handy archive for me  ',0),(2,'node',' software architecture 1 the first step towards building a software with solid architecture is identifying the purpose of that software sounds simple enough but being able to discern such things separates you from hoards of bad programmers in my teenage years my assumption was that software s purpose is to save people time it s suppose to do monotonous and uncreative things that are beneath humans this is a good thesis but it does not encompass the entirety of why we build software if you look at it from a purist s perspective people who track endangered species or smash atoms aren t concerned with time so what is the purpose of building software for them my understanding of this matured with experience recently i found that my evolved thesis resonated with what max kanatalexander wrote in code simplicity the science of software development o reilly copyright 2012 9781449313890 i don t dare try to be as eloquent as kanatalexander so i will use some his words to explain my points the primary purpose of all software is to help people you can break this down into a more specific purpose for your individual piece of software for example an online dictionary exists to help people find meanings for words an accounting software exists to help people keep track of their finances a software that autonomously helps the environment exists to help people to help the environment software doesn t exist to help computers it doesn t exist to help buildings or any other thing the primary purpose of software cannot be  make me money   this motivation does not yield optimal result in any creative profession decartes could not have produced something better than i think therefore i am if someone paid him a million dollar he could not have produced it faster either here is a link detailing what am talking about the purpose of software is certainly not to take people s jobs away new technology shifts jobs and increases net jobs otherwise if we count all the new inventions starting from the invention of the wheel then the net jobs on earth should come out to be zero if you don t agree with this then you might want to learn about the luddites and the luddite fallacy  use the purpose of the software to determine the goals of your software if you are writing a software that allows students to register for courses then your goal is to help students register for courses  you should write down your goal s so there is no miscommunication within your team or between your client and you if your client wants outlandish features then go ahead and humor her as long as those features don t conflict or obscure your goal s when you are buried in work prioritize by determining which feature or bug fix will help people the most if can do this then you have the beginning of a good software that will be appreciated by your client softwarearchitecture softwarearchitectureseries1 ',0),(3,'node',' stand alone zend form example one of the basic tasks of web developers is to build forms however validating each and every form field in php can be tedious i have seen people put the post array through a for loop and try to validate everything in one go but that solution is neither robust nor versatile zend framework has one of the best solution for building secure and versatile forms in php unfortunately it s not transparent how to use the zendform component as a stand alone library without zend mvc in this tutorial i ll try to document how to use zendform with plain php and give the front end person full control over the html 1 first place the zend folder in your working directory you ll find it inside the library folder of your zend framework download 2 then create a create a form